🧾 Manuals & Help
man -k <keyword> → Search command manual by keyword
file file.txt → Identify file type
⏰ Date & Time
date → Show current date/time
alias firstdate='date | tee /home/ubuntu/firstdate.txt | cut --delimiter=" " --fields=1 | tee /home/ubuntu/shortdate | xargs echo hello' → Alias example with date
📂 File & Directory Management
ls → List files and directories
ls -a → List all (including hidden)
ls *.txt → Files ending in .txt
ls ??.txt → Files with exactly 2 chars before .txt
ls file[0-9].txt → Files file0.txt … file9.txt
ls file[A-Z][a-z][0-9].txt → Pattern match
cd → Change directory
. → Current directory
.. → Parent directory
Absolute path → Full path from /
Relative path → Path from current location
touch file.txt → Create empty file/update timestamp
mkdir dir → Create directory
mkdir -p path/to/dir → Create nested directories
mkdir {jan,feb,mar,april}_{2021..2025} → Create multiple directories
touch {jan,feb,mar,april}_{2021..2025}/file{1..100} → 100 files in each dir
rm file1.txt → Remove file
rm *txt → Remove all .txt files
rm *2* → Remove files containing 2
rm *[2,3]* → Remove files containing 2 or 3
rm -r dir → Remove directory recursively
rm -ri dir → Recursive remove with confirmation
rmdir dir → Remove empty directory
cp file1 file2 → Copy file
cp -r dir1 dir2 → Copy directory
mv file1 file2 → Move/rename
nano file.txt → Edit with nano
🔎 Search Files
locate name → Find files by name
locate -i name → Case-insensitive search
locate -i --limit 3 name → Limit results
locate --existing --follow *.conf → Only existing, follow symlinks
find /home/user → Find everything
find . -maxdepth 4 → Limit depth
find . -type f → Files only
find . -type d → Directories only
find . -maxdepth 4 -type d → Limit + dirs
find . -maxdepth 4 -name "*.txt" → Find txt
find . -maxdepth 4 -name "?.txt" → One char name
find . -maxdepth 4 -iname "?.TXT" → Case-insensitive
find / -type f -size +100k | wc -l → Count files >100KB
find / -type f -size +100k -size -5M | wc -l → Count 100KB–5MB
find / -type f -size +100k -size -5M -exec cp {} /home/user/copy_here \; → Copy found files
find / -type f -size +100k -size -5M -ok cp {} /home/user/copy_here \; → Copy with confirmation
📑 File Viewing & Processing
cat file[1..5].txt > output.txt → Combine files
cat file[1..5].txt | tac > reversed.txt → Reverse lines
less file.txt → View with scrolling
find | less → Pipe into pager
head file.txt → First 10 lines
tail file.txt → Last 10 lines
head -n /etc/cups/cups-browsed.conf | tail -n -2 → Show all but last 2 lines
sort file.txt → Sort alphabetically
sort -r file.txt → Reverse sort
sort -u file.txt → Unique sort
↔️ Redirection & Pipes
Standard Input (stdin) → Channel 0 (keyboard input)
Standard Output (stdout) → Channel 1 (normal output)
Standard Error (stderr) → Channel 2 (error messages)
cat 0<input.txt > /dev/pts/1 → Send output to another terminal
cat 1>> output.txt → Append output to file
tty → Show terminal device
date | cut date.txt --delimiter=" " --fields=1 → Pipe + cut
tee → Split output (see + save)
date | tee fulldate.txt | cut --delimiter " " --fields 1 → Tee + cut
xargs → Convert input into command args
cat input.txt | xargs rm input.txt → Delete listed files
alias → Shortcut for commands
📦 Archiving & Compression
tar -cvf archivefile.tar file[1-3].txt → Create tar
tar -xvf archivefile.tar → Extract tar
gzip archivefile.tar → Gzip compress
bzip archivefile.tar → Bzip2 compress
tar -cvzf archivefile.tar.gz file[1-3].txt → Create gzip tar
tar -cvjf archivefile.tar.bz2 file[1-3].txt → Create bzip2 tar
tar -xvzf archivefile.tar.gz → Extract gzip tar
tar -xvjf archivefile.tar.bz2 → Extract bzip2 tar
⚙️ System & Scheduling
bash script → Run a script
crontab -e → Edit cron jobs
ls -lh /etc | head -20 | sort -k 6Mr → List, head, sort
🖥️ System Info
uname → Kernel/system info
lsb_release -a → Distro info
📥 Package Management (APT)
/var/lib/apt/lists → Package list info
/var/cache/apt/archives → Stored .deb files
sudo apt-get update → Update package list
apt-cache search docx → Search packages
apt-cache show docx | less → Package info with pager
sudo apt-get install <pkg> → Install package
sudo apt-get source <pkg> → Download source
sudo apt-get purge <pkg> → Remove package + configs
sudo apt-get autoremove → Remove unused deps
sudo apt-get clean → Remove all cached .deb
sudo apt-get autoclean → Remove only old/unused .deb
